Uses of Class
functions.FunctionPart

  • Packages that use FunctionPart 
    Package Description
    functions
    This package contains all classes nessecary, to work with mathematical functions, with the most important class being Function
    stringConverter
    This package contains all the stuff needed to convert a String to a Function

    • Uses of FunctionPart in functions

      Subclasses of FunctionPart in functions 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  AdditionNexus
      Stores multiple FunctionParts.
      class  Chaining
      This class represents a chaining of two functions, one being the inner function, the second, the outer function.
      This means the result of the inner function will be used as input for the outer function.
      f(x) = f(u(x))
      Note: This FunctionPart returns null in Nexus.getAntiderivative(), because this is extremely complex.
      class  Cos
      This class represents a cosine function with the form f(x) = a*cos(x)
      class  EulerExponentialFunction
      Class representing an exponential function with the e as base
      f(x) = a* e^x
      class  ExponentialFunction
      Class representing a exponential function with the following form:
      f(x) = a*bx
      class  FactorNexus
      Class representing a multiplication of multiple FunctionParts
      This function is constructed like following: f(x) = u(x) * v(x) * ...
      class  Ln
      This class is representing a function with the form f(x)= a*ln(x).
      class  Nexus
      FunctionPart containing multiple other functionParts.
      class  PoweredFunctionPart
      This function represents a FunctionPart powered with a second one.
      class  PowerFunction
      Klasse, welche eine Potenzfunktion der Form f(x) = a*xp repräsentiert.
      class  Sin
      Class representing a sinus function
      f(x) = a * sin(x)
      class  XExponentialFunction
      Class representing a exponential function with base and exponent x
      f(x)= a* xx dar.
